The Rays wrap up the White Sox portion of their Chicago trip this afternoon, trying to avoid a sweep and snap a four-game overall losing streak. J.P. Feyereisen will make his first professional start as the opener, with rookie Tommy Romero expected to work bulk innings in his second pro outing. Game time temperatures are expected in the 30s. Starting Monday, the Rays play three night games against the Cubs. The rotation will be Shane McClanahan on Monday, Josh Fleming (either starting or behind an opener) on Tuesday and Drew Rasmussen on Wednesday. Manager Kevin Cash said Ryan Yarbrough, who initially was expected to be ready to pitch Monday, is still working his way back from groin tightness and has yet to throw off the mound. Cash said they are hoping he will do so in the next day or two, and it was “possible” he would pitch on the homestand which begins Friday. Here is the Rays lineup: And for the White Sox, led by Tampa born Hall of Famer Tony La Russa: • • • Sign up for the Rays Report weekly newsletter to get fresh perspectives on the Tampa Bay Rays and the rest of the majors from sports columnist John Romano. Never miss out on the latest with the Bucs, Rays, Lightning, Florida college sports and more. Follow our Tampa Bay Times sports team on Twitter and Facebook.